"title": "8830: suspicion",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8830",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The belief that people or things are not as they appear. It may be based on evidence, but it can also be ill-founded, occasioned by jealousy or malicious gossip.</p>\n<h2>Suspicion of sexual impurity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:13-Deut22:19\">DEU 22:13–22:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:11-Num5:31\">NUM 5:11–5:31</a></p>\n<h2>Suspicion of drunkenness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:9-1Sam1:18\">1SA 1:9–1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:13-Acts2:15\">ACT 2:13–2:15</a></p>\n<h2>Suspicion of espionage</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam10:1-2Sam10:5\">2SA 10:1–10:5</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Suspicion of treachery</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:6-1Sam18:9\">1SA 18:6–18:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod1:9-Exod1:10\">EXO 1:9–1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:24-1Sam20:31\">1SA 20:24–20:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam21:10-1Sam21:12\">1SA 21:10–21:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam29:1-1Sam29:11\">1SA 29:1–29:11</a></p>\n<h2>Lack of suspicion</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:7-2Sam15:12\">2SA 15:7–15:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam27:1-1Sam27:12\">1SA 27:1–27:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:1-2Sam13:11\">2SA 13:1–13:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:23-2Sam13:29\">2SA 13:23–13:29</a></p>\n<h2>Evil suspicions</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:3-1Tim6:5\">1TI 6:3–6:5</a></strong></p>",
